528c551d710d1efa11114089f60.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104769/96/1047699626_0:0:4964:2793_1280x0_80_0_0_e5aa9417e232221f7db05b0bed05738a.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104769/96/1047699626_0:0:4964:2793_1920x0_80_0_0_c416039bd3e12ce8d382a4acad619622.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / TT NEWS AGENCY / PONTUS LUNDAHL </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊戈尔·库兹涅佐夫</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_kuznetsov_igor/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">军方自己承认，有针对性的广告活动旨在提高其合法性，因为多样性被视为增强能力的一种手段。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">多年来，瑞典武装部队一直致力于增加其组织内的多样性。现在，他们正在尝试一种新方法，即在阿拉伯语新闻网站 Alkompis 上投放有针对性的广告，希望能吸引更多非瑞典背景的员工。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “<strong>我们越不同，我们对敌人就越危险</strong>，”瑞典军方宣称，并进一步声称多样性是有益的，也是增强能力所必需的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “<strong>这场运动的目的是提高武装部队的合法性</strong>，”军方告诉瑞典媒体。<br><br> “多样性和平等最终是关于看待和尊重每个人，也是关于在国防军中创造一种更具包容性的文化。它提高了适应能力——这是在我们生活的瞬息万变的世界中站稳脚跟所必需的——和寻找新的解决方案，”它说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Alkompis 网站将自己描述为“瑞典的阿拉伯语媒体机构，而不是瑞典的阿拉伯语媒体机构”，由前瑞典广播电台的 Mahmoud Agha 于 2012 年创立。它声称是广告资助的，但它也受益于税收减免。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">用阿拉伯语投放有针对性的广告的决定在社交媒体上招致了尖锐的批评。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">曾活跃于绿党和公民大会的约瑟芬·乌塔斯 (Josefin Utas) 说，作为一个不懂阿拉伯语的瑞典语母语者，她不得不求助于一位说阿拉伯语的朋友，她说广告上写着：“我们今天所做的，我们这样做是为了未来。我们在世界形势恶化的阴影下成长、发展和改变。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>约瑟芬乌塔斯补充说：“我写这篇文章是为了告诉你瑞典正在发生的事情。这里还有一些事情要讨论。我们的武装部队使用瑞典人不熟悉的语言交流是否合理？政客们在他们说话时真的是认真的吗？声称移民学习瑞典语很重要？如何在一个日益分裂的国家实现凝聚力。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110510201" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/swedish-military-recruiting-in-arabic-for-the-sake-of-diversity-1110510201.html?share-block=1110510209" data-title="Josefin Utas added: &amp;quot;I am writing this to tell you about what is happening in Sweden. There are also things to discuss here. Is it reasonable for our armed forces to communicate in a language foreign to Swedes? Do politicians really mean it when they claim that it is important for immigrants to learn Swedish? How do you achieve cohesion in a country that is becoming increasingly divided.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这个消息在推特上并不受欢迎，一位用户愤怒地说：“瑞典武装部队用阿拉伯语做广告？首先是 LGBTQ 变装皇后，现在是阿拉伯人。所以他们要保卫瑞典。当阅读童话故事被禁止时，好处就停止了，我们自己去前线还是变装皇后把敌人吓跑？” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110510201" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110509776_0:0:459:445_1440x900_80_0_1_e7f2e77a2ef27bcf92b88ae396462bfa.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110509736" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/swedish-military-recruiting-in-arabic-for-the-sake-of-diversity-1110510201.html?share-img=1110509736"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Photo</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">关于瑞典军方阿拉伯语广告的推文截图</span></div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Screenshot of tweet about Swedish military's ads in Arabic - Sputnik International, 1920, 22.05.2023" title="关于瑞典军方阿拉伯语广告的推文截图" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110509776_0:0:459:445_1920x0_80_0_0_40f7ff3a042826f376a5eb08e24dd041.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%221861%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1861" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110509776_0:0:459:445_640x0_80_0_0_f012492d1d051b768cb54ec11631c8c1.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110509776_0:0:459:445_1280x0_80_0_0_5eb000f1146a2a99e00a5db477191f38.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110509776_0:0:459:445_1920x0_80_0_0_40f7ff3a042826f376a5eb08e24dd041.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet="">关于瑞典军方阿拉伯语广告的推文截图</div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片</div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">另一位网友讽刺地写道：“天哪，我们需要炮灰来应对即将到来的俄罗斯入侵。兄弟，一张通往天堂的机票是承诺的。真诚的，武装部队”，还讽刺了瑞典军方对“ <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230329/here-we-go-again-book-claims-russian-sub-violated-swedish-harbor-in-2017-1108892534.html" target="_blank">俄罗斯入侵”</a>的痴迷“这经常被用作扩大预算的理由。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="media"><div class="article__media"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="photo"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110510201" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110511458_0:0:466:112_1440x900_80_0_1_c8a8cbdd6ee996b9d27da7a23461e891.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1110509718" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/swedish-military-recruiting-in-arabic-for-the-sake-of-diversity-1110510201.html?share-img=1110509718"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"><span class="photoview__copyright"></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">关于瑞典军方阿拉伯语广告的推文截图</span></div></noindex><img media-type="photo" data-source-sid="" alt="Screenshot of tweet about Swedish military's ads in Arabic - Sputnik International, 1920, 22.05.2023" title="关于瑞典军方阿拉伯语广告的推文截图" class=" lazyload" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110511458_0:0:466:112_1920x0_80_0_0_dfb92305832c20e53af8292e0d900d98.jpg" srcset="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20width=%221920%22%20height=%22461%22%3E%3C/svg%3E 100w" decoding="async" width="1920" height="461" data-srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110511458_0:0:466:112_640x0_80_0_0_93e96c5843dcddad1de32d5b5d2728a7.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110511458_0:0:466:112_1280x0_80_0_0_f4a7e6d9d5ffa5b31892772b5515155e.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/16/1110511458_0:0:466:112_1920x0_80_0_0_dfb92305832c20e53af8292e0d900d98.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__description " data-nosnippet="">关于瑞典军方阿拉伯语广告的推文截图</div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">其他人质疑不会说瑞典语的人在武装部队中必须做什么，或者他们应该做出什么贡献。其他人则认为这则广告清楚地证明了武装部队已经变得多么政治化。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此前，瑞典军队公认的人手不足，旨在增加多样性的尝试包括面向女性和广大移民的广告。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">经过十年的大规模移民，在此期间，这个拥有约 1000 万人口的国家仅在 2015 年就接纳了 163,000 名寻求庇护者，阿拉伯语取代芬兰语成为瑞典第二大使用最广泛的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20200819/swedens-newly-founded-arab-party-intends-to-take-responsibility-for-its-people-1080212076.html" target="_blank">母语</a>（估计有 400,000 人说阿拉伯语，约 200,000 人说芬兰语） .除了书展和其他活动外，还有阿拉伯语的当地媒体和国家广播。据报道，阿拉伯语已成为一些幼儿园和学校的<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20201104/swedish-library-staff-drilled-in-arabic-to-facilitate-communication-1080986410.html" target="_blank">主要语言</a>，因为移民社区往往在斯德哥尔摩、哥德堡和马尔默等主要城市及其周边地区形成集群。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 22 May 2023 06:36:59 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/swedish-military-recruiting-in-arabic-for-the-sake-of-diversity-1110510201.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/swedish-military-recruiting-in-arabic-for-the-sake-of-diversity-1110510201.html<category>军队</category><category>瑞典</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>瑞典武装部队</category><category>推特</category><category>军事情报</category><category>阿拉伯</category><category>移民</category><category>斯堪的纳维亚</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[As US Debt Ceiling Talks Enter Crunch Week Wall Street Futures & Asian Stocks Slide]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110510066" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/0b/1108283098_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_f82be9f2fbf205cf0603ba0d637f6030.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1108283080" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/as-us-debt-ceiling-talks-enter-crunch-week-wall-street-futures--asian-stocks-slide-1110510066.html?share-img=1108283080"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Manuel Balce Ceneta</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国国旗于 2023 年 1 月 4 日星期三在华盛顿的美国国会大厦飘扬。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="American flag flies on the U.S. Capitol in Washington, Wednesday, Jan. 4, 2023. - Sputnik International, 1920, 22.05.2023" title="2023 年 1 月 4 日，星期三，美国国旗在华盛顿的美国国会大厦上飘扬。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/0b/1108283098_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_47520085ef1a97010fea1df6ff0fd37a.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/0b/1108283098_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_9041842c0b331a17ca67f121c8dd3f7f.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/0b/1108283098_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_de7589b8d360384558e6a899d0c9bc63.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/03/0b/1108283098_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_47520085ef1a97010fea1df6ff0fd37a.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Manuel Balce Ceneta </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">斯韦特兰娜·埃基缅科</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_svetlana_ekimenko/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:s.ekimenko@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">美国总统拜登在周日离开七国集团 (G7) 峰会之前就债务危机发表了看法。当他谈到他“回家处理”的预算谈判时，拜登用乐观的语气说，“我希望麦卡锡议长在我回家的时候正等着和我谈判。我在等着找出答案。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/us-debt-ceiling-issue-to-undermine-g7-capacity-in-shaping-world---biden-official-1110451884.html#:~:text=US%20Debt%20Ceiling%20Issue%20to%20Undermine%20G7%20Capacity%20in%20Shaping%20World%20%2D%20Biden%20Official" target="_blank">债务上限问题</a>即将进入看似紧要关头的一周，总统乔拜登和众议院议长凯文麦卡锡（加利福尼亚州共和党人）定于周一举行会议，希望打破僵局。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">民主党总统拜登政府一直在与共和党人就提高债务上限问题进行旷日持久的争论，目前债务上限为 31.4 万亿美元。美国在一月份触及法定债务上限，此后一直采取“非常措施”来支付账单。但财政部长珍妮特耶伦周日晚些时候重申，6 月 1 日仍然是<strong>提高债务上限或承担违约风险的最后期限</strong>，否则将“<em>做出艰难的选择</em>”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2">债务上限拉锯战</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">就像拜登可能想把他的注意力从与共和党人的对峙中转移开，并专注于华盛顿在全球舞台上的一些典型的举重，发表有关美国准备“<em>继续向乌克兰提供经济和安全援助的</em>言论”<em>因为它需要</em>”或“<em>帮助台湾</em>”保卫自己免受所谓的中国攻击，国内的麻烦跟着他来到了日本的 G7 峰会。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登不在时，华盛顿发生了一系列活动，但总统似乎一直处于循环之中，与负责领导与共和党谈判的顾问一起参加了 Zoom 电话会议。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">过去几天出现了更多的债务上限拉锯战。 5 月 19 日，国会共和党人<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/republicans-press-pause-on-debt-ceiling-talks-as-june-1-default-deadline-looms-1110469706.html#:~:text=Republicans%20%E2%80%98Press%20Pause%E2%80%99%20on%20Debt%20Ceiling%20Talks%20as%20June%201%20Default%20Deadline%20Looms" target="_blank">退出了谈判</a>，谈判又遇到了民主党拒绝的联邦开支削减问题。数小时后，谈判重回正轨，但周六，共和党人对 2024 年限制军费开支的提议以及一系列国内计划提出异议。最后，众议院议长麦卡锡承认，他们需要等待拜登回来才能取得进展。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我认为我们可以达成协议。我从一开始就一直在争论的部分内容是需要考虑税收结构以及削减开支。我愿意削减开支，我提议削减和开支超过一万亿美元，”拜登在回家前的新闻发布会上说，并补充说，“我不能保证他们 [共和党人] 不会通过做一些令人发指的事情来迫使违约。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110510066" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/as-us-debt-ceiling-talks-enter-crunch-week-wall-street-futures--asian-stocks-slide-1110510066.html?share-block=1110510072" data-title="&quot;I think that we can reach an agreement. Part of what I've been arguing from the beginning is a need to consider the tax structure as well as cutting spending. I'm willing to cut spending, and I proposed cuts and spending of over a trillion dollars,&quot; Biden said during a press conference before heading home, adding that, &quot;I can't guarantee that they [Republicans] wouldn't force a default by doing something outrageous.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在总统乘坐空军一号返回华盛顿期间，拜登和麦卡锡通了电话。麦卡锡周日在美国国会大厦被记者问及这次通话时说： </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们的团队今天正在讨论，我们准备（原文如此）明天开会。这比之前好多了。所以，是的。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110510066" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/as-us-debt-ceiling-talks-enter-crunch-week-wall-street-futures--asian-stocks-slide-1110510066.html?share-block=1110510074" data-title="&quot;Our teams are talking today and we're setting (sic) to have a meeting tomorrow. That's better than it was earlier. So, yes.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">众议院议长补充说： </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “没有达成协议。我们仍然分开。我正在看的是我们的分歧在哪里以及我们如何解决这些分歧，我觉得那部分是富有成效的。”。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110510066" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/as-us-debt-ceiling-talks-enter-crunch-week-wall-street-futures--asian-stocks-slide-1110510066.html?share-block=1110510456" data-title="&quot;There's no agreement. We're still apart. What I'm looking at are where our differences are and how could we solve those, and I felt that part was productive.&quot;."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">乔·拜登还表示，与麦卡锡的通话“<em>进行得很顺利</em>”，并补充说，“<em>我们明天再谈</em>。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据白宫高级顾问史蒂夫·里凯蒂透露，周日晚上，双方工作人员在麦卡锡位于国会大厦的办公室里进行了两个多小时的谈判，并补充说，“<em>今晚我们将继续工作</em>。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">事实上，在过去几周的激烈言辞之后，拜登和麦卡锡的言论似乎都显得更加积极。乔·拜登 (Joe Biden) 曾表示，共和党议员并不反对看到美国违约，只是为了在他 2024 年的连任选举中发言。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="social" data-social="telegram"><div class="article__tg"></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据麦卡锡的说法，共和党人准备支持增加国防预算，同时削减总体开支。他补充说，前总统唐纳德特朗普通过的减税措施并未包括在债务上限谈判中。据报道，拜登政府提议确保明年非国防可自由支配支出持平，没有减少或增加的空间。非国防可自由支配支出由立法者通过拨款法案控制，具体规定了可以为某些政府项目提供多少资金。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">乔·拜登一直坚持需要一项“干净的”债务上限法案，而不是在 2024 年预算中强制削减预算——这是提高债务上限的典型方式。然而，他最近暗示愿意在最后期限迫近的情况下进行谈判。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">两党的支持势在必行，因为共和党在众议院占微弱多数，而拜登的民主党对参议院的控制微乎其微。随着时间的流逝，拜登和麦卡锡周一的会晤距离财政部的最后期限仅剩 10 天。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">经济专家一直警告说，政府债务违约对美国经济和国际市场都将是灾难性的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">事实上，对违约的担忧已经在打压市场。华尔街期货和亚洲股市周一下跌。标准普尔 500 指数期货早盘下跌 0.1%，而纳斯达克期货持平。 MSCI 在日本以外的亚太地区最广泛指数也持平，而日本日经指数下跌 0.11%。香港恒生指数同样下跌约 40 点。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 22 May 2023 06:25:02 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/as-us-debt-ceiling-talks-enter-crunch-week-wall-street-futures--asian-stocks-slide-1110510066.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/as-us-debt-ceiling-talks-enter-crunch-week-wall-street-futures--asian-stocks-slide-1110510066.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>凯文麦卡锡</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category><category>共和党人</category><category>金库</category><category>民主党人</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[China Summons Japanese Ambassador Over Statements Made at G7 Summit]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110509482" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110255131_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_08fcc47d6a64c8f66958df187c328bb4.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110255112" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/china-summons-japanese-ambassador-over-statements-made-at-g7-summit-1110509482.html?share-img=1110255112"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / KAZUHIRO NOGI</span> <span 